						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">Banshaku wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">Emulators don't reproduce that unknown state for CHR-RAM so I never saw that behavior.</div><br /><br />Most emulators I've looked at default to setting mapper regs to swap in the first 8K of CHR like you expected.  I never understood why they did that -- as it just seems to encourage bad behavior for homebrewers/rom hackers.<br /><br />I defaulted to zeroing regs in my emu (which would have produced a glitch similar to what you posted) and ran into no problems with any commercial games I tried.  So yeah... who knows what the deal with that is.<br /><br />Just goes to show you -- can't always trust emulators.<br /><br /><div class="quotetitle"><b>Quote:</b></div><div class="quotecontent">By the way, I'm not sure what kind of advantage you could have to switch banks in ram thought. Any commercial games use it for some specific effects?</div>
<br />
<br />Lagrange Point comes to mind.  I don't think it does any actual effects with it (like you, I fail to see the point), but I know it relies on that behavior.</div>

